From: Chenghai Huang <huangchenghai2@huawei.com>
Date: Sun, 7 Apr 2024 15:59:58 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] crypto: hisilicon/sec - Fix memory leak for sec resource
 release
References: bsc#1218260
Patch-mainline: 6.6.36
Git-commit: bba4250757b4ae1680fea435a358d8093f254094

[ Upstream commit bba4250757b4ae1680fea435a358d8093f254094 ]

The AIV is one of the SEC resources. When releasing resources,
it need to release the AIV resources at the same time.
Otherwise, memory leakage occurs.

The aiv resource release is added to the sec resource release
function.

Signed-off-by: Chenghai Huang <huangchenghai2@huawei.com>
Signed-off-by: Herbert Xu <herbert@gondor.apana.org.au>
Signed-off-by: Sasha Levin <sashal@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Robert Frohl <rfrohl@suse.com>
---
 drivers/crypto/hisilicon/sec2/sec_crypto.c | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/crypto/hisilicon/sec2/sec_crypto.c b/drivers/crypto/hisilicon/sec2/sec_crypto.c
index c3a630cb27a6..932cc277eb3a 100644
--- a/drivers/crypto/hisilicon/sec2/sec_crypto.c
+++ b/drivers/crypto/hisilicon/sec2/sec_crypto.c
@@ -478,8 +478,10 @@ static void sec_alg_resource_free(struct sec_ctx *ctx,
 
 	if (ctx->pbuf_supported)
 		sec_free_pbuf_resource(dev, qp_ctx->res);
-	if (ctx->alg_type == SEC_AEAD)
+	if (ctx->alg_type == SEC_AEAD) {
 		sec_free_mac_resource(dev, qp_ctx->res);
+		sec_free_aiv_resource(dev, qp_ctx->res);
+	}
 }
 
 static int sec_alloc_qp_ctx_resource(struct hisi_qm *qm, struct sec_ctx *ctx,
